programme.title: Bowhunting with Triplepoint Outdoors at Crystal Creek Bowhunting
programme.desc: In Episode 2 of Season 4 of Huntech Pro, the team joined forces with Triplepoint Outdoors at Crystal Creek Bowhunting. Josh Miller, owner of Triplepoint Outdoors, put his broadheads to the test, yielding remarkable results by taking down a Baboon using the Bear Redemption. Employing the Ravin R500, he skillfully executed a challenging shot on an Impala ram with a tough quartering angle, getting a full passthrough with his 100gr ClovisTM mechanical broadhead. He displayed his prowess and targeted and successfully hunted an aged kudu Cow. The episode showcased strategic hunting techniques, expert equipment usage, and unforgettable moments in the heart of the wild, making it a thrilling chapter in the Huntech Pro journey.

programme.title: Hunting with Triplepoint Outdoors at Roger Berger Safaris
programme.desc: In the third thrilling installment of Huntech Pro Season 4, our intrepid hunting team ventured into the heart of the Free State Province in South Africa, where they embarked on an unforgettable safari at Roger Berger Safaris. This particular location was a paradise for any avid hunter, boasting vast open spaces that stretched as far as the eye could see. The landscape was nothing short of breathtaking, with rolling hills, sweeping savannas, and an abundance of game animals that called this pristine wilderness home. One highlight of this extraordinary episode was the introduction of a groundbreaking hunting innovation. The owner of Triplepoint Outdoors, Josh Miller, took center stage to showcase his revolutionary creation, the ClovisTM 100gr mechanical broadhead. This cutting-edge mechanical broadhead promised a new era in hunting, and our team was eager to put it to the test. With the Free State Province's abundant wildlife at their disposal, our Huntech Pro team set out to evaluate the ClovisTM 100gr mechanical broadhead in real-world hunting scenarios. This meant taking on some of Africa's most formidable and majestic creatures, including the formidable Watusi, the elusive Kudu, the regal Roan antelope, and even the formidable Cape Buffalo. However, it wasn't just about the innovative technology. The episode also captured the personal triumphs of our dedicated Huntech Pro Staff members. Beulah Smit achieved a remarkable milestone, as she proudly took her first Fallow Deer, marking a special moment in her hunting journey. Host Johan Smit also had his share of excitement as he pushed the limits of his brand-new Tikka UPR 6.5 Creedmoor rifle on a challenging White Blesbuck hunt. The precision and performance of the rifle would be put to the test in this high-stakes adventure, showcasing the art of long-range shooting. With breathtaking landscapes, a revolutionary mechanical broadhead, thrilling encounters with big game animals, and personal hunting achievements, Episode 3 of Huntech Pro Season 4 at Roger Berger Safaris in the Free State Province, South Africa, was an unforgettable adventure for the ages. This episode left viewers eagerly anticipating what other incredible hunting experiences lay in store for the remainder of the season.
